@miraep8, I do not think it has to do with `test_check_X_enforce_min_columns`.

Why: `test_check_X_enforce_min_columns` is the last test in the lexicographic order. `pytest-xdist` splits the list of tests in two, along with lexicographic order. So if one of the two workers gets stuck (above: gw0), the other one (above:gw1) still works through all the tests on their chunk, and hence the last test the non-stuck worker (above: gw1) encounters will be the innocent `test_check_X_enforce_min_columns`.

My hypothesis is, `pytest-xdist` incorrectly reports the last test started as the cause of an error, assuming that it is always the last test started causing the error. Of course, if you have two workers, and one is stuck for a long time, the actual cause would be the last test that *the stuck worker* encounters. Which would be the Facebook Prophet related test, or the one that comes after it in the lexicographic order.
